summaries.short: After a welcome from Issa Rae, the cast sits down with Kamie Crawford to bond and look toward the future. But just when the group seems ready to move on, lingering resentments surface – and someone from their past keeps them on their toes.
summaries.full: After a surprise welcome from Executive Producer Issa Rae, the friends come together with Host Kamie Crawford to chop it up over audience hot takes, the drama of televising their lives, and the fallout of holding one another accountable. As the group attempts to hammer out unresolved issues, someone from their past threatens to disturb the fragile peace – leaving them to wonder, "Are they even friends?”

summaries.short: Success is in the air as P’Jae’s block party goes off without a hitch - but as the crew confronts simmering conflicts, the future of their friendships remains uncertain.
summaries.full: At a photoshoot for Cheryl’s fashion line, Ty confronts a defensive Jerrold about his role in the podcast drama. Later, insight from Jordan’s mom prompts him to clear the air with Jay. Though the block party finds P’Jae in his element, the festivities are cut short as simmering conflicts threaten to tear the crew apart.

summaries.full: While planning his upcoming block party, Ty and Amanda hold P’Jae accountable for his actions in Cabo. Jerrold’s podcast creates a safe space for the guys to talk about mental health, but things get heated when the discussion turns to finances and privilege. Later, Bri and Jordan search for romance outside the friend group.

summaries.short: Ty wrangles Candiss’ over-the top-drama as Cheryl’s alter-ego makes an appearance. Bri connects with Kam after Jordan leaves her high and dry… again. P’Jae gets clarity on his relationship.
summaries.full: The Cabo party gets wild as Cheryl’s alter ego makes an appearance and Ty wrangles Candiss’ over-the-top drama. After Jordan leaves her high and dry yet again, Bri connects with Kam. Later, P’Jae throws Becky for a loop.
